## Definition of done

### Red phase
- [ ] At least one failing test was written before any implementation
- [ ] The failing test was committed (or at least run to confirm failure)

### Green phase
- [ ] The minimum implementation was written to make the test pass
- [ ] No additional features were added during the green phase

### Refactor phase
- [ ] Code was refactored for clarity, removing duplication and improving naming
- [ ] Tests remained green throughout every refactor step
- [ ] Refactor commits are separate from implementation commits

### Test coverage
- [ ] Happy-path test present
- [ ] Error/edge-case tests present
- [ ] Property-based tests added for security-critical or complex logic
- [ ] `cargo test --doc` passes (doc examples are valid)

### Code quality
- [ ] `cargo fmt --check` passes
- [ ] `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` passes (zero warnings)
- [ ] `cargo test` passes (all tests green, no regressions)
- [ ] No `unwrap()` or `expect()` in non-test production code

### Safety
- [ ] No new `unsafe` blocks without a `// SAFETY:` comment

